Any time I read any 17th century medical text I am genuinely in awe at how clearpilled they are. Sciatica? Give them laxative oil, put them in a hot bath, donkey milk, bloodletting. Pleurisy? Same stuff. Purgatives, laxatives, diuretics. It's always the same stuff no matter what.

Melancholic Humours? Feces in the blood. Give them diarrhea with a herb then later put them in a warm seawater bath. Then give them hiera picra bitters made of aloe and cinnamon. It mostly acts as a purgative you guessed it. Just variations of these for any disease you think of.

It's obvious it's just anti-endotoxin and moving the intestine, reducing the transit time. Castor oil can do it, but even advanced drugs like Rapamycin probably basically have the same mechanism at the core (speeds transit, improves barrier function). They really figured it out!
